0;font-size:14px;color:#14532d;line-height:1.7;\">\n            <strong>1. TSM trim:</strong> Execute 0.112 share trim at market open or on a bounce. Net +$2.67 locked. Don't try to time it within a day.<br>\n            <strong>2. AMD decision:</strong> Make the hold vs. full exit call in the morning. If holding, set a mental stop at $493 (TP1 level) — if it falls back there, exit then. If exiting, sell at open.<br>\n            <strong>3. AVGO:</strong> No action until $421.57. Hard stop at $379 — if touched, exit immediately regardless of commission math (stop overrides all rules).<br>\n            <strong>4. NVDA + LLY:</strong> Nothing to do.\n          </p>\n        </td>\n      </tr></table>\n    </td></tr>\n\n    <!-- EDUCATION MODULE -->\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:0 24px 24px;\">\n      <table role=\"presentation\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"background:#f1f5f9;border-radius:8px;\"><tr>\n        <td style=\"padding:20px 24px;\">\n          <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:11px;color:#475569;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;\">&#128218; Today you learned</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:8px 0 0;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#0f172a;\">Earnings Whisper Numbers</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:12px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:#1e293b;line-height:1.7;\">AVGO gave you a real-time masterclass today. Official sellside consensus was $2.32 EPS. AVGO printed $2.44 — a +5% beat. The stock fell 14%. The buyside had two whisper expectations that mattered more than the headline number: (1) raise the $100B AI guidance for 2026, and (2) confirm the full AI integrated systems strategy. CEO Tan delivered neither. Guidance stayed flat; systems play was walked back to chips-only. The headline reads &ldquo;AVGO beats estimates&rdquo; — the market heard &ldquo;guidance unchanged, strategy backpedalled.&rdquo; Sellside consensus is the floor. The buyside whisper is the actual bar. For AMD on August 4: before that print, check whether the buyside whisper is running 10-15% above published consensus. If it is, the stock needs to beat the whisper magnitude, not just the number, to hold its gains.</p>\n          <p style=\"margin:12px 0 0;font-size:12px;color:#475569;font-style:italic;\">Also today: <em>Expectations beat</em> — beating the published EPS estimate is table stakes; what moves the stock is beating the expected magnitude of the beat, not just the bar itself.</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr></table>\n    </td></tr>\n\n    <!-- FOOTER -->\n    <tr><td style=\"padding:16px 24px 24px;border-top:1px solid #f3f4f6;\">\n      <p style=\"margin:0;font-size:10px;color:#9ca3af;line-height:1.5;\">Research output, not financial advice. Past performance does not guarantee future results. Verify halal compliance quarterly on Zoya or Musaffa. NVDA/AVGO/TSM/AMD prices from web search (Yahoo Finance, CNBC, MarketBeat) as of June 4, 2026. LLY price estimated from intraday data — verify before trading. Generated 4 June 2026, 11:05 PM Kuwait Time (AST, UTC+3).</p>\n    </td></tr>\n\n  </table>\n  </td></tr>\n</table>\n</body>\n</html>"
